Because we grew up eating breakfast tacos—whether from a local taco joint or wrapped fresh by our mom in the morning—one of our favorite ways to enjoy breakfast is rolled up in a tortilla! Here, we’ve made a Tortilla Breakfast Roll for you to enjoy in the morning. Think: Omelet meets taco meets wrap. ¡Buen provecho!⁠
⁠
Ingredients⁠
2 tbsp Avocado Oil⁠
½ Roma Tomato, small diced⁠
½ Jalapeño, minced⁠
⅛ Onion, small diced⁠
3 Eggs⁠
Salt and Pepper to taste⁠
Grain Free Almond Flour Tortillas⁠
Habanero Hot Sauce⁠
Fresh Cilantro⁠
⁠
Directions⁠
1. In a 8-10 inch non-stick skillet, add oil, tomatoes, jalapeños, and onions. Sauté for 5 minutes. In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs together, season with salt and pepper, and add to the skillet.⁠
2. Spread egg mixture to create a round ‘omelet’, large enough to cover the whole surface of a tortilla.⁠
3. Once the open-faced omelet has cooked through, place tortilla over it and flip over in the pan. Tortilla will now be directly on the pan.⁠
4. Cook on medium heat for 1-2 minutes until tortilla starts to get some color. Remove from heat onto a cutting board and roll tortilla with omelet inside.⁠
5. Cut tortilla roll into 4 smaller pieces and garnish with hot sauce and cilantro.⁠
⁠

It can be hard to convince a little one to choose broccoli over macaroni or carrots over chicken nuggets. (We know this because we've all been that "little one.") But, we’ve taken our experience and memories of hiding our peas and carrots in our napkins under the dining table and then sneakily dropping them for scavenging pets to eat the evidence... and created our own yummy solution! Our Chicken Veggie Nuggets are breaded in our Grain Free Sea Salt Tortilla Chips, look like traditional chicken nuggets, AND they satisfy a parent’s wish for their children to eat their veggies! 🥕⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Ingredients⁠⁠
1 bag Siete Grain Free Sea Salt Tortilla Chips, finely crushed ⁠⁠
1 lb Chicken Breast ⁠⁠
1 cup Steamed Vegetables (We used a combination of carrots, cauliflower, & broccoli.) ⁠⁠
½ tbsp Dried Minced Garlic ⁠⁠
1 ½ tsp Salt ⁠⁠
¼ tsp Black Pepper ⁠⁠
Oil for deep frying ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Directions⁠⁠
1. Preheat a large deep skillet such as a cast-iron skillet)  halfway with oil or deep fryer to 325F.⁠⁠
2. In a food processor, add chicken, vegetables, and seasonings. Blend until it becomes a fine puree. Stop and scrape the sides down along the way to puree vegetables as much as possible and mix thoroughly with the chicken. ⁠⁠
3. Use a cookie sheet or large platter to spread finely crushed tortilla chips. ⁠⁠
4. Using a tablespoon measurement, scoop out each nugget into a circle onto the chip crumbs. Press down gently to make a “nugget shape” and toss nuggets in chips to coat all sides. Repeat with the remaining mixture. ⁠⁠
5. Fry for 8-9 minutes until crispy and internal temperature is over 165F. ⁠⁠
6. Serve with ketchup or favorite condiment. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
For more heritage-inspired meals for the whole family, head to the link in our bio! 💜 ⁠⁠
⁠⁠

🍨 We’re so excited to feature our Chamoy Botana Sauce and Chile Lime Seasoning in @gati.icecream’s new ice cream flavor, Melon Chamoy Chile Lime, and in their latest Ice Cream Sundae, Chile Lime Chamoy Sundae! 🍨

Gati uses seasonal canary melons from Mission San Juan Farm and creamy coconut milk to make this new flavor with Chamoy and Chile Lime! You can order it by the cup, cone, or pint. And their unique and refreshing sundae features their beloved Mango Lime flavor—plus, it’s made-to-order and served with sticky rice and fresh mango. Take it from us, both options are soooo delicious! Try them at Gati while supplies last right here in Austin, Texas!

Fun fact: The Mango Lime flavor was born when founder, Jam, had leftover mangoes from her restaurant. That flavor was a hit and launched their whole ice cream line! We’re stoked to pair our products with this tasty creation. 😄💗

Our hearts go out to our Hill Country and Williamson County familia across Kerrville, Hunt, and Ingram, the neighboring communities, the broader Texas region, and all who have been affected by the devastating floods. Texas is our home, it’s familia, and right now, our home and our familia are hurting. We’ve taken a moment to hold space for grieving, mindful that anything we say feels small compared to the magnitude of the unimaginable loss.  We are immensely grateful to all the brave first responders, volunteers, and to the organizations and community members contributing time, sharing resources, and donating supplies across the state. These actions are a testament to the ways that we are truly better together—because community is everything. 

We are also so grateful for the ways in which organizations like @treatyoak, @bouldinacres, @austinpetsalive, @12foxbeer, @southaustinbeergarden and @texaschildrensatx have allowed us and others to partner with them in supporting our community during this heartbreaking time. If you know of more organizations currently accepting product drop-off donations, please share in the comments or feel free to DM us. In the meantime, we wanted to highlight ways to help—check out our stories for more info.  ♥️
